Description: The set of gene and transcript annotations used in expression quantification.
URL referring to the exact gene annotation used

Attribute: RSeQC - Fraction Supporting Read 1 From Sense Strand
Description: Fraction of reads explained by the following scenarios: read 1 mapped to sense strand indicates parental gene on sense strand, read 1 mapped to antisense strand indicates parental gene on antisense strand, read 2 mapped to sense strand indicates parental gene on antisense strand, or read 2 mapped to antisense strand indicates parental gene on sense strand. Generated by RSeQC (infer_experiment.py).

Attribute: RSeQC - Fraction Supporting Read 1 From Antisense Strand
Description: Fraction of reads explained by the following scenarios: read 1 mapped to sense strand indicates parental gene on antisense strand, read 1 mapped to antisense strand indicates parental gene on sense strand, read 2 mapped to sense strand indicates parental gene on sense strand, read 2 mapped to antisense strand indicates parental gene on antisense strand. Generated by RSeQC (infer_experiment.py).
Fraction of reads that were mapped to genome regions without standedness of transcripts (such as regions that having both strands transcribed). Generated by RSeQC (infer_experiment.py).
Percentage of known (i.e., with both splice sites being annotated) splicing events. Generated by RSeQC (junction_annotation.py).

Percentage of novel (i.e., with no annotated splice sites) splicing events. Generated by RSeQC (junction_annotation.py).
Percentage of known (i.e., with both splice sites being annotated) splicing junctions. Generated by RSeQC (junction_annotation.py).

Attribute: RSeQC - Percent Partial Novel Splicing Junctions
